124
00:05:11.875 --> 00:05:14.615
So including Maori Pacifica children

125
00:05:14.715 --> 00:05:17.175
and families affected by disabilities.

126
00:05:19.075 --> 00:05:23.255
Uh, that type of engagement, um, will help to build enduring

127
00:05:23.765 --> 00:05:25.935
two-way relationships that are really important

128
00:05:25.955 --> 00:05:28.535
for best tailoring services to meet the needs

129
00:05:28.535 --> 00:05:30.775
of those groups to address inequities

130
00:05:31.035 --> 00:05:32.175
and actually helping services

131
00:05:32.235 --> 00:05:33.815
to work together effectively as well.

132
00:05:35.115 --> 00:05:36.895
And finally, while the range

133
00:05:36.955 --> 00:05:39.735
of measures in place is best practice

134
00:05:40.195 --> 00:05:43.815
and the reports are useful, uh, we know that they're complex

135
00:05:43.955 --> 00:05:45.575
and they can be difficult to understand,

136
00:05:45.995 --> 00:05:49.975
and agencies had started to make some simplifications

137
00:05:49.975 --> 00:05:52.295
to the way they communicated with the public,

138
00:05:52.635 --> 00:05:54.295
and we are just encouraging agencies

139
00:05:54.355 --> 00:05:55.575
to keep working on the way

140
00:05:55.575 --> 00:05:58.245
that they communicate changes in rates of child poverty.

141
00:05:58.945 --> 00:06:01.445
Um, and that's really just so both the public

142
00:06:01.505 --> 00:06:03.165
